                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Mizner</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-08-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 1, 1890</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Minister Mizner telegraphs from Menton to Minister Ryan, to be communicated to
                    the Secretary of State, that he is in direct communication with San José, both
                    by telegraph and railroad, and can communicate with naval officers there, the
                    distance being about 70 miles. Telegraph lines do not pass through San José,
                    except the branch from Menton, which latter place is headquarters.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
